{
  "stem": "2391.3",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] And my, my father went to talk to the Mother Superior.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she says, send your daughter here to school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You don't have to pay, you know, free of charge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And don't tell anybody you're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He told her.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But she says, nobody should-- has to know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And so I went to-- I went to Mass and I went to confess.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I went, I did everything, just trying to figure out how to do it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And you know, trying to blend in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I learned a lot about Catholicism.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And so officially, we were Catholic, because, you know, that was the official religion there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The mayor.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name was, instead of Eva Cohn, became Jacqueline Moulin, which sounded very French.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, I liked the name Jacqueline.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my first daughter, my first born, I named her Jacqueline in memory of this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Also, I think it's a nice name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she never knew that, only after I showed her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Just recently, I showed her that, that fake identity card.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She said, now I know why my name is Jacqueline.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And he actually suggested it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was his idea, the mayor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because, he says, you know, it's not safe with the name Cohn.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because the situation became, gradually, more and more dangerous.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "At first it was a little more relaxed, but it became more and more dangerous.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we knew a group of Jews in Macon who lived in that area.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we would always meet with them, and we would always talk.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You know, tragedy kind of draws you together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they practically-- gradually, they were all arrested and disappeared.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were practically the only ones left when the war was over, of that group of Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
